N:ralphmode
D:[ralphmode] Apply permission profile for Claude Code (or Codex/Gemini) to reduce approval popups during ralph/jeo automation. Runs apply-ralphmode.sh automatically: detects repo root, writes .claude/settings.json with acceptEdits+denylist (repo) or bypassPermissions (sandbox), creates ~/.claude/hooks/ralph-safety-check.sh if missing. Key safety rule: repo preset by default; sandbox only for disposable environments.
G:ralph permissions automation claude-code codex-cli gemini-cli sandbox bypass trusted-folders denylist jeo

U[5]:
  When approval popups break flow while repeatedly running ralph or jeo
  When you need to align Claude Code, Codex CLI, and Gemini CLI settings for the same repo
  When you must separate repo-scoped automation from true YOLO mode
  When expanding automation while keeping guardrails for .env/secrets/destructive shell commands
  When you need to check current ralphmode status (bash apply-ralphmode.sh --status)

S[5]{n,action,details}:
  1,Detect-Mode,Parse user message: sandbox/yolo/bypass-all → MODE=sandbox; everything else → MODE=repo (default)
  2,Run-Script,Run: bash scripts/apply-ralphmode.sh --mode $MODE (writes .claude/settings.json + ensures safety hook)
  3,Inline-Fallback,If script not found: apply Python inline preset (repo: acceptEdits+deny-list; sandbox: bypassPermissions)
  4,Verify-Hook,Confirm ~/.claude/hooks/ralph-safety-check.sh exists; create if missing (blocks rm -rf, force-push, sudo, .env access)
  5,Report-Revert,Tell user: preset applied, file path, allow/deny list, restart-required, revert command (rm .claude/settings.json)

R[5]:
  Default mode is repo (acceptEdits + deny-list); sandbox mode requires explicit user request
  Script location: .agent-skills/ralphmode/scripts/apply-ralphmode.sh (also ~/.agent-skills/... or ~/.claude/skills/...)
  Check status without changes: bash apply-ralphmode.sh --status
  For Codex sandbox runs: codex -c model_reasoning_effort="high" --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox -c model_reasoning_summary="detailed" -c model_supports_reasoning_summaries=true
  Gemini sandbox: gemini --yolo (combines sandbox + auto-approve; disposable environments only)

E[4]{desc,in,out}:
  "Claude Code repo preset","ralphmode (no sandbox keyword)","Writes .claude/settings.json with acceptEdits + deny-list for .env/rm-rf/sudo/force-push"
  "Claude Code sandbox preset","ralphmode sandbox","Writes .claude/settings.json with bypassPermissions; for disposable environments only"
  "Codex CLI sandbox flags","ralphmode codex sandbox","codex -c model_reasoning_effort=high --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox -c model_reasoning_summary=detailed -c model_supports_reasoning_summaries=true"
  "Gemini YOLO mode","ralphmode gemini sandbox","gemini --yolo — combines sandbox + auto-approve for disposable-sandbox ralph runs"
